{
  "video_id": "acikxzM6GaY",
  "title": "Who belongs in a city? |  OluTimehin Adegbeye",
  "es": 0,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 12995.0,
      "end_time": 17900.0,
      "text": "Cities are like siblings in a large polygamous family."
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 18193.0,
      "end_time": 22572.0,
      "text": "Each one has a unique personality and is headed in a distinct direction."
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 23290.0,
      "end_time": 25445.0,
      "text": "But they all have somewhat shared origins."
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 26497.0,
      "end_time": 29544.0,
      "text": "Sometimes I think postcolonial cities are like the children"
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 29568.0,
      "end_time": 31267.0,
      "text": "of the two least-favorite wives,"
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 31291.0,
      "end_time": 32875.0,
      "text": "who are constantly being asked,"
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 32899.0,
      "end_time": 35102.0,
      "text": "\"Ah, why can&#39;t you be more like your sister?\""
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 35126.0,
      "end_time": 36736.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 38101.0,
      "end_time": 41711.0,
      "text": "The \"why\" of cities is largely the same, no matter where they are:"
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 42312.0,
      "end_time": 46431.0,
      "text": "an advantageous location that makes trade and administration possible;"
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 46456.0,
      "end_time": 48648.0,
      "text": "the potential for scalable opportunities"
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 48672.0,
      "end_time": 51490.0,
      "text": "for the skilled and unskilled alike;"
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 51730.0,
      "end_time": 54920.0,
      "text": "a popular willingness to be in constant flux"
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 54116.0,
      "end_time": 55869.0,
      "text": "and, of course, resilience."
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 56587.0,
      "end_time": 59418.0,
      "text": "The \"how\" of cities, however, is a whole other story."
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 59995.0,
      "end_time": 61698.0,
      "text": "How are they run?"
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 61722.0,
      "end_time": 63515.0,
      "text": "How do they grow?"
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 63539.0,
      "end_time": 66417.0,
      "text": "How do they decide who belongs and who doesn&#39;t?"
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 67571.0,
      "end_time": 69349.0,
      "text": "Lagos is my home."
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 70360.0,
      "end_time": 72310.0,
      "text": "You can always find the Nigerians"
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 72550.0,
      "end_time": 74285.0,
      "text": "by following the noise and the dancing, right?"
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 74309.0,
      "end_time": 75445.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 75469.0,
      "end_time": 79309.0,
      "text": "Like any major city, that place is a lot of things,"
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 79333.0,
      "end_time": 81632.0,
      "text": "many of which are highly contradictory."
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 82370.0,
      "end_time": 84466.0,
      "text": "Our public transportation doesn&#39;t quite work,"
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 84490.0,
      "end_time": 87645.0,
      "text": "so we have these privately owned bright yellow buses"
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 87669.0,
      "end_time": 89704.0,
      "text": "that regularly cause accidents."
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 90555.0,
      "end_time": 94902.0,
      "text": "Luxury car showrooms line badly maintained and often flooded roads."
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 95558.0,
      "end_time": 98377.0,
      "text": "Street evangelism is only slightly less ubiquitous"
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 98401.0,
      "end_time": 99865.0,
      "text": "than street harassment."
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 100525.0,
      "end_time": 103747.0,
      "text": "Sex workers sometimes have two degrees, a bank job"
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 103771.0,
      "end_time": 105579.0,
      "text": "and a prominent role in church."
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 105603.0,
      "end_time": 106607.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 106631.0,
      "end_time": 107793.0,
      "text": "On any given day,"
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 107817.0,
      "end_time": 111145.0,
      "text": "there can be either a party or a burned body"
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 111170.0,
      "end_time": 112565.0,
      "text": "in the middle of a street."
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 114544.0,
      "end_time": 117325.0,
      "text": "There is so much that is possible in Lagos"
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 117349.0,
      "end_time": 118539.0,
      "text": "and so much that isn&#39;t,"
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 118563.0,
      "end_time": 121776.0,
      "text": "and very often the difference between possibility and impossibility"
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 121800.0,
      "end_time": 123414.0,
      "text": "is simply who you are,"
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 123438.0,
      "end_time": 125957.0,
      "text": "and if you&#39;re lucky enough, who you&#39;re connected to."
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 126672.0,
      "end_time": 128860.0,
      "text": "Belonging in Lagos is a fluid concept"
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 128883.99999999999,
      "end_time": 133120.0,
      "text": "determined by ethnic origin, sexual orientation, gender,"
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 133370.0,
      "end_time": 136372.0,
      "text": "but most visibly and often most violently,"
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 136396.0,
      "end_time": 137704.0,
      "text": "class."
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 138312.0,
      "end_time": 140913.0,
      "text": "Before Nigeria became a country,"
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 140937.0,
      "end_time": 144848.0,
      "text": "fisherpeople from the inland creeks started to come down the Lagos lagoon"
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 144872.0,
      "end_time": 147246.0,
      "text": "and establish villages along the coast."
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 147840.0,
      "end_time": 152274.0,
      "text": "About 60 years later, my grandfather, Oludotun Adekunle Kukoyi,"
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 152298.0,
      "end_time": 153820.0,
      "text": "also arrived in Lagos."
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 154487.0,
      "end_time": 157903.0,
      "text": "Like me, he was an alumnus of the University of Ibadan,"
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 157927.0,
      "end_time": 161462.0,
      "text": "a young member of the educated elite in the independence era."
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 162820.0,
      "end_time": 165674.0,
      "text": "Over time, he built an illustrious career as a land surveyor,"
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 165699.0,
      "end_time": 167765.0,
      "text": "mapping out now-bustling neighborhoods"
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 167789.0,
      "end_time": 170300.0,
      "text": "when they were just waist-high wild grass."
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 171173.0,
      "end_time": 172579.0,
      "text": "He died when I was nine."
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 172603.0,
      "end_time": 176390.0,
      "text": "And by that time, my family, like the families of those fisherpeople,"
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 176414.0,
      "end_time": 177959.0,
      "text": "knew Lagos as home."
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 179953.0,
      "end_time": 182184.0,
      "text": "Among the Yoruba, we have a saying,"
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 182208.0,
      "end_time": 184678.0,
      "text": "\"Èkó gb’olè, ó gb’ọ̀lẹ,\""
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 184702.0,
      "end_time": 188417.0,
      "text": "which can be translated to mean that Lagos will welcome anyone."
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 189337.0,
      "end_time": 191775.0,
      "text": "But that saying is becoming less and less true."
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 192784.0,
      "end_time": 195929.0,
      "text": "Many Lagosians, including the descendants of those fisherpeople"
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 195953.0,
      "end_time": 198305.0,
      "text": "who arrived generations before my grandfather,"
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 198329.0,
      "end_time": 200430.0,
      "text": "are now being pushed out"
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 200670.0,
      "end_time": 201770.0,
      "text": "to make room for an emergent city"
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 201794.0,
      "end_time": 204389.0,
      "text": "that has been described as \"the new Dubai.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 205321.0,
      "end_time": 209427.0,
      "text": "You see, Lagos inspires big dreams, even in its leaders,"
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 209451.0,
      "end_time": 212135.0,
      "text": "and successive governments have declared aspirations"
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 212159.0,
      "end_time": 214962.0,
      "text": "towards a megacity where poverty does not exist."
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 216330.0,
      "end_time": 219585.0,
      "text": "Unfortunately, instead of focusing on the eradication of poverty"
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 219610.0,
      "end_time": 221113.0,
      "text": "as you would expect,"
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 221137.0,
      "end_time": 224670.0,
      "text": "the strategy of choice focuses on eliminating the poor."
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 227590.0,
      "end_time": 229195.0,
      "text": "Last October, the Governor announced plans"
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 229219.0,
      "end_time": 232743.0,
      "text": "to demolish every single waterfront settlement in Lagos."
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 233703.0,
      "end_time": 236258.0,
      "text": "There are more than 40 of these indigenous communities"
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 236282.0,
      "end_time": 237444.0,
      "text": "all over the city,"
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 237468.0,
      "end_time": 239584.0,
      "text": "with over 300,000 people living in them."
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 240623.0,
      "end_time": 242247.0,
      "text": "Otodo Gbame,"
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 242271.0,
      "end_time": 244237.0,
      "text": "a hundred-year-old fishing village"
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 244261.0,
      "end_time": 247195.0,
      "text": "with a population about three-quarters that of Monaco"
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 247219.0,
      "end_time": 249856.0,
      "text": "and similar potential for beachfront luxury --"
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 249880.0,
      "end_time": 250912.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 250937.0,
      "end_time": 252902.0,
      "text": "was one of the first to be targeted."
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 254513.0,
      "end_time": 257891.0,
      "text": "I first heard of Otodo Gbame after the demolition started."
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 258654.0,
      "end_time": 262796.0,
      "text": "When I visited in November 2016, I met Magdalene Aiyefoju."
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 263943.0,
      "end_time": 265558.0,
      "text": "She is a now-homeless woman"
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 265583.0,
      "end_time": 267918.0,
      "text": "whose surname means, \"the world is blind.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 269341.0,
      "end_time": 273232.0,
      "text": "Magdalene&#39;s son Basil was one of over 20 people"
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 273256.0,
      "end_time": 275800.0,
      "text": "who were shot, drowned"
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 275105.0,
      "end_time": 277249.0,
      "text": "or presumed dead in that land grab."
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 279452.0,
      "end_time": 282961.0,
      "text": "Standing outside her shelter, I saw the two white-sand football fields"
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 282985.0,
      "end_time": 284475.0,
      "text": "where Basil used to play."
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 285470.0,
      "end_time": 289109.0,
      "text": "Spread all around us were the ruins of schools, churches,"
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 289133.0,
      "end_time": 291253.0,
      "text": "a primary health center, shops,"
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 291277.0,
      "end_time": 292818.0,
      "text": "thousands of homes."
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 293712.0,
      "end_time": 297200.0,
      "text": "Young children enthusiastically helped to put up shelters,"
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 297225.0,
      "end_time": 300280.0,
      "text": "and about 5,000 of the residents, with nowhere else to go,"
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 300304.0,
      "end_time": 301727.0,
      "text": "simply stayed put."
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 302658.0,
      "end_time": 304760.0,
      "text": "And then in April,"
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 304773.0,
      "end_time": 306886.0,
      "text": "state security personnel came back."
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 308490.0,
      "end_time": 311530.0,
      "text": "This time, they cleared the community out completely,"
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 311554.0,
      "end_time": 314375.0,
      "text": "with beatings, bullets and fire."
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 315787.0,
      "end_time": 320272.0,
      "text": "As I speak, there are construction crews preparing Otodo Gbame&#39;s beaches"
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 320297.0,
      "end_time": 323485.0,
      "text": "for anyone who can afford a multi-million-dollar view."
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 324420.0,
      "end_time": 326883.0,
      "text": "The new development is called \"Periwinkle Estate.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 330208.0,
      "end_time": 335990.0,
      "text": "Forced evictions are incredibly violent and, of course, unconstitutional."
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 335123.0,
      "end_time": 338416.0,
      "text": "And yet, they happen so often in so many of our cities,"
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 338440.0,
      "end_time": 342185.0,
      "text": "because the first thing we are taught to forget about poor people"
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 342209.0,
      "end_time": 343632.0,
      "text": "is that they are people."
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 344412.0,
      "end_time": 347794.0,
      "text": "We believe that a home is a thing a person absolutely has a right to,"
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 347819.0,
      "end_time": 350793.0,
      "text": "unless the person is poor and the home is built a certain way"
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 350817.0,
      "end_time": 352166.0,
      "text": "in a certain neighborhood."
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 352711.0,
      "end_time": 356149.0,
      "text": "But there is no single definition of the word \"home.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "start_time": 357270.0,
      "end_time": 360510.0,
      "text": "After all, what is a slum besides an organic response"
    },
    {
      "index": 116,
      "start_time": 360535.0,
      "end_time": 363621.0,
      "text": "to acute housing deficits and income inequality?"
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "start_time": 364631.0,
      "end_time": 367813.0,
      "text": "And what is a shanty if not a person making a home for themselves"
    },
    {
      "index": 118,
      "start_time": 367838.0,
      "end_time": 369404.0,
      "text": "against all odds?"
    },
    {
      "index": 119,
      "start_time": 371150.0,
      "end_time": 373527.0,
      "text": "Slums are an imperfect housing solution,"
    },
    {
      "index": 120,
      "start_time": 373551.0,
      "end_time": 377244.0,
      "text": "but they are also prime examples of the innovation, adaptability"
    },
    {
      "index": 121,
      "start_time": 377268.0,
      "end_time": 379994.0,
      "text": "and resilience at the foundation --"
    },
    {
      "index": 122,
      "start_time": 380180.0,
      "end_time": 381405.0,
      "text": "and the heart --"
    },
    {
      "index": 123,
      "start_time": 381429.0,
      "end_time": 383940.0,
      "text": "of every functional city."
    },
    {
      "index": 124,
      "start_time": 384303.0,
      "end_time": 386654.0,
      "text": "You don&#39;t need to be the new Dubai"
    },
    {
      "index": 125,
      "start_time": 386678.0,
      "end_time": 388248.0,
      "text": "when you&#39;re already Lagos."
    },
    {
      "index": 126,
      "start_time": 389369.0,
      "end_time": 395358.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    },
    {
      "index": 127,
      "start_time": 396771.0,
      "end_time": 398817.0,
      "text": "We have our own identity,"
    },
    {
      "index": 128,
      "start_time": 398841.0,
      "end_time": 400541.0,
      "text": "our own rhythm,"
    },
    {
      "index": 129,
      "start_time": 400565.0,
      "end_time": 402860.0,
      "text": "and as anyone who knows Lagos can tell you,"
    },
    {
      "index": 130,
      "start_time": 402884.0,
      "end_time": 406420.0,
      "text": "poor Lagosians are very often the source of the city&#39;s character."
    },
    {
      "index": 131,
      "start_time": 406928.0,
      "end_time": 409677.0,
      "text": "Without its poor, Lagos would not be known for its music"
    },
    {
      "index": 132,
      "start_time": 409701.0,
      "end_time": 410979.0,
      "text": "or its endless energy"
    },
    {
      "index": 133,
      "start_time": 411300.0,
      "end_time": 414652.0,
      "text": "or even the fact that you can buy an ice cold drink or a puppy"
    },
    {
      "index": 134,
      "start_time": 414676.0,
      "end_time": 416790.0,
      "text": "through your car window."
    },
    {
      "index": 135,
      "start_time": 416103.0,
      "end_time": 418711.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 136,
      "start_time": 420219.0,
      "end_time": 423640.0,
      "text": "The conditions that cause us to define certain neighborhoods as slums"
    },
    {
      "index": 137,
      "start_time": 423664.0,
      "end_time": 425635.0,
      "text": "can be effectively improved,"
    },
    {
      "index": 138,
      "start_time": 425659.0,
      "end_time": 428722.0,
      "text": "but not without recognizing the humanity and the agency"
    },
    {
      "index": 139,
      "start_time": 428746.0,
      "end_time": 430286.0,
      "text": "of the people living in them."
    },
    {
      "index": 140,
      "start_time": 431120.0,
      "end_time": 434380.0,
      "text": "In Lagos, where public goods are rarely publicly available,"
    },
    {
      "index": 141,
      "start_time": 434620.0,
      "end_time": 437664.0,
      "text": "slum dwellers are often at the forefront of innovating solutions."
    },
    {
      "index": 142,
      "start_time": 438460.0,
      "end_time": 440921.0,
      "text": "After being disconnected from the grid for months"
    },
    {
      "index": 143,
      "start_time": 440946.0,
      "end_time": 444211.0,
      "text": "because the power company couldn&#39;t figure out how to collect bills,"
    },
    {
      "index": 144,
      "start_time": 444235.0,
      "end_time": 447696.0,
      "text": "one settlement designed a system that collectivized remittances"
    },
    {
      "index": 145,
      "start_time": 447720.0,
      "end_time": 450349.0,
      "text": "and got everyone cheaper rates into the bargain."
    },
    {
      "index": 146,
      "start_time": 451488.0,
      "end_time": 453634.0,
      "text": "Another settlement created a reform program"
    },
    {
      "index": 147,
      "start_time": 453658.0,
      "end_time": 456412.0,
      "text": "that hires local bad boys as security."
    },
    {
      "index": 148,
      "start_time": 456436.0,
      "end_time": 458561.0,
      "text": "They know every trick and every hideout,"
    },
    {
      "index": 149,
      "start_time": 458586.0,
      "end_time": 462160.0,
      "text": "so now troublemakers are more likely to get caught and reported to police"
    },
    {
      "index": 150,
      "start_time": 462400.0,
      "end_time": 465367.0,
      "text": "and fewer of the youth end up engaging in criminal activity."
    },
    {
      "index": 151,
      "start_time": 466860.0,
      "end_time": 468253.0,
      "text": "Yet another settlement recently completed"
    },
    {
      "index": 152,
      "start_time": 468277.0,
      "end_time": 471390.0,
      "text": "a flood-safe, eco-friendly communal toilet system."
    },
    {
      "index": 153,
      "start_time": 472860.0,
      "end_time": 474986.0,
      "text": "Models like these are being adopted across Lagos."
    },
    {
      "index": 154,
      "start_time": 476264.0,
      "end_time": 479693.0,
      "text": "Informal settlements are incorrectly named as the problem."
    },
    {
      "index": 155,
      "start_time": 480374.0,
      "end_time": 483799.0,
      "text": "In fact, the real problems are the factors that create them,"
    },
    {
      "index": 156,
      "start_time": 483823.0,
      "end_time": 485756.0,
      "text": "like the entrenchment of poverty,"
    },
    {
      "index": 157,
      "start_time": 485780.0,
      "end_time": 486974.0,
      "text": "social exclusion"
    },
    {
      "index": 158,
      "start_time": 486999.0,
      "end_time": 488426.0,
      "text": "and state failures."
    },
    {
      "index": 159,
      "start_time": 489206.0,
      "end_time": 491828.0,
      "text": "When our governments frame slums as threats"
    },
    {
      "index": 160,
      "start_time": 491852.0,
      "end_time": 494741.0,
      "text": "in order to justify violent land grabs or forced evictions,"
    },
    {
      "index": 161,
      "start_time": 494766.0,
      "end_time": 497731.0,
      "text": "they&#39;re counting on those of us who live in formal housing"
    },
    {
      "index": 162,
      "start_time": 497755.0,
      "end_time": 501553.0,
      "text": "to tacitly and ignorantly agree with them."
    },
    {
      "index": 163,
      "start_time": 502455.0,
      "end_time": 504472.0,
      "text": "Rather, we must remind them"
    },
    {
      "index": 164,
      "start_time": 504497.0,
      "end_time": 507118.0,
      "text": "that governments exist to serve not only those who build"
    },
    {
      "index": 165,
      "start_time": 507142.0,
      "end_time": 508645.0,
      "text": "and live in luxury homes,"
    },
    {
      "index": 166,
      "start_time": 508669.0,
      "end_time": 511460.0,
      "text": "but also those who clean and guard them."
    },
    {
      "index": 167,
      "start_time": 512429.99999999994,
      "end_time": 513201.99999999994,
      "text": "Our --"
    },
    {
      "index": 168,
      "start_time": 513226.0,
      "end_time": 516587.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    },
    {
      "index": 169,
      "start_time": 517625.0,
      "end_time": 519837.0,
      "text": "our realities may differ,"
    },
    {
      "index": 170,
      "start_time": 519861.0,
      "end_time": 521842.0,
      "text": "but our rights don&#39;t."
    },
    {
      "index": 171,
      "start_time": 523941.00000000006,
      "end_time": 525614.0,
      "text": "The Lagos state government,"
    },
    {
      "index": 172,
      "start_time": 525638.0,
      "end_time": 527561.0,
      "text": "like far too many on our continent,"
    },
    {
      "index": 173,
      "start_time": 527585.0,
      "end_time": 530258.0,
      "text": "pays lip service to ideas of inclusion,"
    },
    {
      "index": 174,
      "start_time": 530282.0,
      "end_time": 533329.0,
      "text": "while acting as though progress can only be achieved"
    },
    {
      "index": 175,
      "start_time": 533353.0,
      "end_time": 536785.0,
      "text": "by the erasure, exploitation and even elimination of groups"
    },
    {
      "index": 176,
      "start_time": 536809.0,
      "end_time": 538568.0,
      "text": "it considers expendable."
    },
    {
      "index": 177,
      "start_time": 539718.0,
      "end_time": 543194.0,
      "text": "People living with disabilities who hawk or beg on Lagos streets"
    },
    {
      "index": 178,
      "start_time": 543219.0,
      "end_time": 545414.0,
      "text": "are rounded up, extorted"
    },
    {
      "index": 179,
      "start_time": 545438.0,
      "end_time": 546651.0,
      "text": "and detained."
    },
    {
      "index": 180,
      "start_time": 547155.0,
      "end_time": 549393.0,
      "text": "Women in low-income neighborhoods are picked up"
    },
    {
      "index": 181,
      "start_time": 549417.0,
      "end_time": 550912.0,
      "text": "and charged with prostitution,"
    },
    {
      "index": 182,
      "start_time": 550936.0,
      "end_time": 553820.0,
      "text": "regardless of what they actually do for a living."
    },
    {
      "index": 183,
      "start_time": 553844.0,
      "end_time": 558363.0,
      "text": "Gay citizens are scapegoated to distract from real political problems."
    },
    {
      "index": 184,
      "start_time": 559751.0,
      "end_time": 563355.0,
      "text": "But people, like cities, are resilient,"
    },
    {
      "index": 185,
      "start_time": 563912.0,
      "end_time": 567317.0,
      "text": "and no amount of legislation or intimidation or violence"
    },
    {
      "index": 186,
      "start_time": 567341.0,
      "end_time": 569276.0,
      "text": "can fully eliminate any of us."
    },
    {
      "index": 187,
      "start_time": 570128.0,
      "end_time": 573766.0,
      "text": "Prostitutes, women and women who work as prostitutes"
    },
    {
      "index": 188,
      "start_time": 573790.0,
      "end_time": 575300.0,
      "text": "still haven&#39;t gone extinct,"
    },
    {
      "index": 189,
      "start_time": 575325.0,
      "end_time": 577981.0,
      "text": "despite centuries of active suppression."
    },
    {
      "index": 190,
      "start_time": 578714.0,
      "end_time": 581345.0,
      "text": "Queer Africans continue to exist,"
    },
    {
      "index": 191,
      "start_time": 581369.0,
      "end_time": 585154.0,
      "text": "even though queerness is now criminalized in most parts of the continent."
    },
    {
      "index": 192,
      "start_time": 585178.0,
      "end_time": 589727.0,
      "text": "And I&#39;m fairly certain that poor people don&#39;t generally tend to just disappear"
    },
    {
      "index": 193,
      "start_time": 589751.0,
      "end_time": 592478.0,
      "text": "because they&#39;ve been stripped of everything they have."
    },
    {
      "index": 194,
      "start_time": 593255.0,
      "end_time": 596692.0,
      "text": "We are all already here,"
    },
    {
      "index": 195,
      "start_time": 596716.0,
      "end_time": 598955.0,
      "text": "and that answers the question"
    },
    {
      "index": 196,
      "start_time": 598979.0,
      "end_time": 600784.0,
      "text": "of whether or not we belong."
    },
    {
      "index": 197,
      "start_time": 603584.0,
      "end_time": 606698.0,
      "text": "When those fisherpeople started to sail down the lagoon"
    },
    {
      "index": 198,
      "start_time": 606722.0,
      "end_time": 608156.0,
      "text": "in search of new homes,"
    },
    {
      "index": 199,
      "start_time": 608181.0,
      "end_time": 610244.0,
      "text": "it could not have occurred to them"
    },
    {
      "index": 200,
      "start_time": 610268.0,
      "end_time": 612392.0,
      "text": "that the city that would rise up around them"
    },
    {
      "index": 201,
      "start_time": 612416.0,
      "end_time": 615145.0,
      "text": "would one day insist that they do not belong in it."
    },
    {
      "index": 202,
      "start_time": 616645.0,
      "end_time": 618837.0,
      "text": "I like to believe that my grandfather,"
    },
    {
      "index": 203,
      "start_time": 618861.0,
      "end_time": 620726.0,
      "text": "in mapping new frontiers for Lagos,"
    },
    {
      "index": 204,
      "start_time": 620750.0,
      "end_time": 622661.0,
      "text": "was trying to open it up"
    },
    {
      "index": 205,
      "start_time": 622685.0,
      "end_time": 625699.0,
      "text": "to make room for other people to be welcomed by the city"
    },
    {
      "index": 206,
      "start_time": 625723.0,
      "end_time": 627382.0,
      "text": "in the same way that he was."
    },
    {
      "index": 207,
      "start_time": 628548.0,
      "end_time": 631393.0,
      "text": "On my way here, my grandma called me"
    },
    {
      "index": 208,
      "start_time": 631417.0,
      "end_time": 634154.0,
      "text": "to remind me how proud she was,"
    },
    {
      "index": 209,
      "start_time": 634178.0,
      "end_time": 637170.0,
      "text": "how proud [my grandfather] and my mother would have been."
    },
    {
      "index": 210,
      "start_time": 637555.0,
      "end_time": 640132.0,
      "text": "I am their dreams come true."
    },
    {
      "index": 211,
      "start_time": 641283.0,
      "end_time": 646277.0,
      "text": "But there is no reason why their dreams -- or mine, for that matter --"
    },
    {
      "index": 212,
      "start_time": 646301.0,
      "end_time": 647673.0,
      "text": "are allowed to come true"
    },
    {
      "index": 213,
      "start_time": 647697.0,
      "end_time": 650131.0,
      "text": "while those of others are turned to nightmares."
    },
    {
      "index": 214,
      "start_time": 651120.0,
      "end_time": 652637.0,
      "text": "And lest we forget:"
    },
    {
      "index": 215,
      "start_time": 653204.0,
      "end_time": 655402.0,
      "text": "the minimum requirement for a dream"
    },
    {
      "index": 216,
      "start_time": 656151.0,
      "end_time": 658311.0,
      "text": "is a safe place to lay your head."
    },
    {
      "index": 217,
      "start_time": 661628.0,
      "end_time": 663615.0,
      "text": "It is too late now for Basil,"
    },
    {
      "index": 218,
      "start_time": 664365.0,
      "end_time": 666264.0,
      "text": "but not for Magdalene,"
    },
    {
      "index": 219,
      "start_time": 666288.0,
      "end_time": 668227.0,
      "text": "not for the hundreds of thousands,"
    },
    {
      "index": 220,
      "start_time": 668251.0,
      "end_time": 670645.0,
      "text": "the millions still under threat in Lagos"
    },
    {
      "index": 221,
      "start_time": 670669.0,
      "end_time": 672387.0,
      "text": "or any of our cities."
    },
    {
      "index": 222,
      "start_time": 673188.0,
      "end_time": 676140.0,
      "text": "The world does not have to remain blind"
    },
    {
      "index": 223,
      "start_time": 676380.0,
      "end_time": 680467.0,
      "text": "to the suffering that is created when we deny people&#39;s humanity,"
    },
    {
      "index": 224,
      "start_time": 680491.0,
      "end_time": 683781.0,
      "text": "or even to the incredible potential for growth that exists"
    },
    {
      "index": 225,
      "start_time": 683805.0,
      "end_time": 687825.0,
      "text": "when we recognize and value all contributions."
    },
    {
      "index": 226,
      "start_time": 689199.0,
      "end_time": 691814.0,
      "text": "We must hold our governments"
    },
    {
      "index": 227,
      "start_time": 691838.0,
      "end_time": 693543.0,
      "text": "and ourselves"
    },
    {
      "index": 228,
      "start_time": 693567.0,
      "end_time": 694987.0,
      "text": "accountable"
    },
    {
      "index": 229,
      "start_time": 695110.0,
      "end_time": 698718.0,
      "text": "for keeping our shared cities safe for everyone in them,"
    },
    {
      "index": 230,
      "start_time": 699912.0,
      "end_time": 702101.0,
      "text": "because the only cities worth building --"
    },
    {
      "index": 231,
      "start_time": 702125.0,
      "end_time": 706830.0,
      "text": "indeed, the only futures worth dreaming of --"
    },
    {
      "index": 232,
      "start_time": 706107.0,
      "end_time": 708140.0,
      "text": "are those that include all of us,"
    },
    {
      "index": 233,
      "start_time": 708829.0,
      "end_time": 711820.0,
      "text": "no matter who we are"
    },
    {
      "index": 234,
      "start_time": 711106.0,
      "end_time": 713433.0,
      "text": "or how we make homes for ourselves."
    },
    {
      "index": 235,
      "start_time": 714279.0,
      "end_time": 715467.0,
      "text": "Thank you."
    },
    {
      "index": 236,
      "start_time": 715491.0,
      "end_time": 720185.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    }
  ]
}